.SH NAME
simple_shell - a simple command-line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
simple_shell

.SH DESCRIPTION
The simple_shell program is a command-line
interpreter that reads input from the user and
executes the commands entered.
The program is designed to run on Linux-based
operating systems and is written in the C programming language.

.SH OPTIONS
There are no options for the simple_shell program.

.SH USAGE
The simple_shell program is used by invoking
the executable file from the command line.
Once the program is running, the user can enter commands
to be executed. The program will display a prompt
and wait for the user to enter a command.
The command lines are simple, no semicolons,
no pipes, no redirections or any other advanced features.
The command lines are made only of one word.
No arguments will be passed to programs.

The program will continue to loop until the
user enters Ctrl+D to indicate the end of input.

.SH ERRORS
If an executable cannot be found, the program will
print an error message and display the prompt again.

.SH SEE ALSO
sh(1), bash(1), zsh(1), csh(1)

